 <title>Java in instrument control software</title>
 <link>https://sea.ucar.edu/forums/java-instrument-control-software</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;I&#039;m an advocate of using Java.  I use Java and IDL in the instrument data processing pipelines I create.  I&#039;ve seen Java used more and more over the recent years in astronomical image processing and pipelines.  The European Space Agency has a number of interesting projects in development primarily using Java.

It&#039;s also interesting that Java is being used in realtime instrument control systems in astronomy.  I&#039;ve learned of this in several international projects.  The big ATST solar telescope project is advocating its use.

&lt;a href=&quot;http://adsabs.harvard.edu/full/2000ASPC..216..271A&quot;&gt;Here&#039;s an older paper&lt;/a&gt; on using XML and Java in this context.

